id: pm-ir9vqy
title: "GH-634: successful global reinstall can remove the pm executable"
description: "A successful npm global install can be followed by manifest_missing and a missing pm executable while npm still reports @unbrained/pm-cli installed, leaving recovery dependent on another reinstall."
type: Issue
status: open
priority: 1
tags[6]: "area:install","area:release",bundle-integrity,concurrency,github-report,security
created_at: "2026-07-21T20:58:17.040Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-22T18:25:02.558Z"
author: codex-relationship-backfill-20260721
estimated_minutes: 240
acceptance_criteria: "Global install publication keeps executable, bundle, and manifest generation coherent; manifest_missing recovery never removes the only executable; concurrent or interrupted install behavior has real temp-prefix tests; npm/global-prefix diagnostics provide an actionable safe retry"
parent: pm-ugqx
severity: critical
environment: Linux npm global prefix
repro_steps: "Install @unbrained/pm-cli@2026.7.21 globally, run a repository command, observe bundle_integrity_torn_install manifest_missing, then observe the pm executable missing while npm list still reports the package."
expected_result: A successful install atomically exposes one coherent executable/bundle/manifest generation.
actual_result: The package remained registered but the global pm executable disappeared until reinstall.
affected_version: 2026.7.21
component: install-bundle-publication
regression: false
customer_impact: Every pm workflow is unavailable until the operator discovers and performs another reinstall.
